# The `DefinitionGenerator` Class Reference

<DoxygenPage pluginConfig={pluginConfig}>

## Public Member Functions

### tryToGenerate() {#a7a66069c05f745e4e6c1303b810395ca}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>virtual Error llvm::orc::DefinitionGenerator::tryToGenerate (<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/orc/lookupstate">LookupState</a> &amp; LS, <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/orc/#ac17672ae6b70c781cc77713e88d698eb">LookupKind</a> K, <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/orc/jitdylib">JITDylib</a> &amp; JD, <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/orc/#a7cb1d8cb0ab2329f032d69d79498c81d">JITDylibLookupFlags</a> JDLookupFlags, <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/aarch64/aarch64promoteconstant-cpp/#a90f8350fecae261c25be85d38b451bff">const</a> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/orc/symbollookupset">SymbolLookupSet</a> &amp; LookupSet)</>}>
DefinitionGenerators should override this method to insert new definitions into the parent <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/orc/jitdylib">JITDylib</a>.

K specifies the kind of this lookup. JD specifies the target <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/orc/jitdylib">JITDylib</a> being searched, and JDLookupFlags specifies whether the search should match against hidden symbols. Finally, Symbols describes the set of unresolved symbols and their associated lookup flags.
